{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "<p data-start=\"521\" data-end=\"772\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">This course explores </span></span><strong data-start=\"542\" data-end=\"654\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">how AI, blockchain, virtual reality, extended reality, and other emerging technologies are reshaping society</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> . The focus is not on the technical details but on their </span></span><strong data-start=\"711\" data-end=\"769\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">societal, ethical, economic, and cultural implications</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> .</span></span></p><p data-start=\"774\" data-end=\"1079\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Rather than following a fixed curriculum, this is a </span></span><strong data-start=\"826\" data-end=\"871\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">student-driven, presentation-based course</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> . Students will </span></span><strong data-start=\"887\" data-end=\"918\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">conduct first-hand research</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> and present findings on how these technologies impact </span></span><strong data-start=\"973\" data-end=\"1076\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">education, industry, medicine, politics, art, music, robotics, the economy, governance, and culture</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> .</span></span></p><p data-start=\"1081\" data-end=\"1290\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Since </span></span><strong data-start=\"1087\" data-end=\"1123\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">technology evolves unpredictably</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> , this syllabus serves only as a </span></span><strong data-start=\"1156\" data-end=\"1171\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">placeholder</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> —students will shape the course content in real time, responding to current events, breakthroughs, and controversies.</span></span></p>", "到達目標": "<p data-start=\"1321\" data-end=\"1375\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">By the end of this course, students will be able to:</span></span></p><ol data-start=\"1376\" data-end=\"1986\"><li data-start=\"1376\" data-end=\"1502\"><strong data-start=\"1379\" data-end=\"1402\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Analyze and present</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> how AI, blockchain, VR/XR, and other disruptive technologies impact different aspects of society.</span></span></li><li data-start=\"1503\" data-end=\"1610\"><strong data-start=\"1506\" data-end=\"1527\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Critically assess</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> the ethical, economic, and political consequences of technological advancements.</span></span></li><li data-start=\"1611\" data-end=\"1723\"><strong data-start=\"1614\" data-end=\"1643\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Understand and anticipate</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> future trends in AI, automation, digital identity, and decentralized systems.</span></span></li><li data-start=\"1724\" data-end=\"1850\"><strong data-start=\"1727\" data-end=\"1752\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Engage in discussions</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> on the societal challenges and opportunities of integrating these technologies into daily life.</span></span></li><li data-start=\"1851\" data-end=\"1986\"><strong data-start=\"1854\" data-end=\"1893\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Develop independent research skills</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> to explore the real-world effects of emerging technologies beyond theoretical discussions.</span></span></li></ol>", "特記事項": "【合併】The Web &amp; Society（総合政策学部）/ウェブと社会（総合政策学部）", "関連科目": "", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "<p data-start=\"2016\" data-end=\"2077\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">This is a </span></span><strong data-start=\"2026\" data-end=\"2074\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">presentation-based, discussion-driven course</span></span></strong><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> .&nbsp; It is in bilingual format in English and Japanese.&nbsp; Although a face-to-face course, all classes will also be broadcast via Zoom and recorded for later viewing.&nbsp; But, it an absolute requirement to attend in person to at least 12 of the 15 classes.</span></span></p><ul data-start=\"2078\" data-end=\"2492\"><li data-star